How to Upload Excel file to Power BI desktop 6

Download the file going to this link  

http://datasets.wri.org/dataset/globalpowerplantdatabase

-Open Power bi desktop if you don’t have power BI desktop you can download it by the link below

https://powerbi.microsoft.com/en-us/get-started/?&OCID=AID719832_SEM_M2kNt4pL&lnkd=Google_PowerBI_Brand&gclid=Cj0KCQjw1pblBRDSARIsACfUG11CaX5Dpn0-vx8ucUtHhNGUQWbZB4plK5ef_wcdkUF5wtPT1hG8MzkaAmeTEALw_wcB

Now our aim is to get the excel data (CSV) to the power bi desktop so that we can build our report.
1/ Click on Get data icon

2/Then click excel file

3/ Search for  excel file you have downloaded

4/Then  click open 

5/Click load  or transform if you want to make some editing to your data
